  MeshShadowMode: None
  ShadowColor: {x: 1.000000, y: 1.000000, z: 1.000000, w: 1.000000}
  ShadowDensity: 1.000000
  Text: |-
    This series of examples demonstrates different approaches to creating spatial image and video effects.
    
    1. Spatial Image API 
    
    This API takes an image as input, converts it into a spatial representation, and returns a mesh.
    Multiple meshes can be enabled one at a time to create and play a full sequence.
    The API is powered by the Remote Service Gateway.
    
    2. Gaussian Splatting
    
    This local feature takes a .ply file as input and renders it as a spatial scene.
    By clicking the “+” icon in the Asset Browser and selecting “Gaussian Splatting from .ply files,” you can import a sequence of .ply files and play them back as a spatial video.
    
    3. Experimental Depth Estimation
    
    This system runs locally using an .onnx model to estimate depth from images.
    It generates a 3D representation of each frame by predicting depth and displaying it in three dimensions.
    
    To get started enable one example at the time and learn about the utility in the inspector panel
